I"1<h1 id="deploy-your-site">Deploy your site</h1>

<p>Docusaurus is a <strong>static-site-generator</strong> (also called <strong><a href="https://jamstack.org/">Jamstack</a></strong>).</p>

<p>It builds your site as simple <strong>static HTML, JavaScript and CSS files</strong>.</p>

<h2 id="build-your-site">Build your site</h2>

<p>Build your site <strong>for production</strong>:</p>

<div class="language-bash highlighter-rouge"><div class="highlight"><pre class="highlight"><code><table class="rouge-table"><tbody><tr><td class="rouge-gutter gl"><pre class="lineno">1
</pre></td><td class="rouge-code"><pre>npm run build
</pre></td></tr></tbody></table></code></pre></div></div>

<p>The static files are generated in the <code class="highlighter-rouge">build</code> folder.</p>

<h2 id="deploy-your-site-1">Deploy your site</h2>

<p>Test your production build locally:</p>

<div class="language-bash highlighter-rouge"><div class="highlight"><pre class="highlight"><code><table class="rouge-table"><tbody><tr><td class="rouge-gutter gl"><pre class="lineno">1
</pre></td><td class="rouge-code"><pre>npm run serve
</pre></td></tr></tbody></table></code></pre></div></div>

<p>The <code class="highlighter-rouge">build</code> folder is now served at <code class="highlighter-rouge">http://localhost:3000/</code>.</p>

<p>You can now deploy the <code class="highlighter-rouge">build</code> folder <strong>almost anywhere</strong> easily, <strong>for free</strong> or very small cost (read the <strong><a href="https://docusaurus.io/docs/deployment">Deployment Guide</a></strong>).</p>
:ET